ST PETERSBURG - Polyus, Russia's largest gold producer, said on Thursday its 2018 production was likely to be at the upper end of the forecast range of 2.375-million to 2.425-million troy ounces. Speaking on the sidelines of the St Petersburg economic forum, Polyus CEO Pavel Grachev also said the company's capital expenditures were expected to be slightly below the initially planned $850-million this year.